		{
			dependencies: ["PS01000000000024"]
			description: ["Flux Network storage blocks act as wireless RF batteries on the network — they absorb surplus from Flux Plugs and release it on demand to Flux Points. Basic Flux Storage provides a modest buffer. Herculean Flux Storage holds ten times more. Gargantuan Flux Storage holds one hundred times the base capacity and is the practical cap for most setups. Add Flux Storage to your network before the Powah Reactor or Large Combustion Engine — the burst charging on startup will otherwise saturate Flux Points before storage can buffer it. A Gargantuan array ensures even large power spikes are absorbed cleanly."]
